				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A 29F010 or 29F040 might work. The program would occupy half of the eight sectors, and the rest would rotate among these functions: <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>User data </li><li>More user data </li><li>Revisions to user data, as they are written </li><li>Area that will get erased and filled with a copy of sector a, b, or c, whichever has most deleted revisions </li></ol>
<br />The user would see only enough capacity to fill two of these four sectors.
<br />
<br />But a mapper designed for use with a 29F040 would need either a fixed bank at $E000-$FFFF or a good reset detector to reset the program bank so that a CPU reset never starts the program counter in a freshly erased sector.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

