					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I just finished a <a href="http://pineight.com/nes/#password_save" class="postlink">demo of password generation, entry, and validation</a>.
<br />
<br />The NVSRAM that blargg mentioned is $7.50 each, compared to $2.50 each for an ordinary 62256.
<br />
<br />The method of splitting a 29F040 between game and save would appear to need a custom mapper that places its registers below $6000 so as to distinguish flash writes from mapper writes.
<br />
<br />On #nesdev, someone suggested Ramtron FRAM. But parallel FRAMs are considered obsolete according to Ramtron's web site, and IÂ²C FRAMs appear to need mapper support (even if only an open-collector latch so that the CPU can bit-bang it).</div>

